[ddp_help]
15AA65451FBB7AB4=DDP es una Marca Registrada por DCA Inc., 1989-2008 +++
14DD675D5210D84D=The DDP format is used to prepare archivos for audio CD manufacturing.
576732C3CB3333EB=Please set the render Salida format to 44100Hz, 16-bit, stereo.  +++
6E31FBF60BEAADC6=This is the only format supported by audio CDs. +++
82CF900DE12BC8D8=DDP Salida consists of many archivos, all of which must be sent to the CD manufacturer. +++
F5C80E027AAF25F0=For standard CDs, the Red Book specification includes these limitations: +++
F61BBD6C2D754F6D=- at least one pista +++
F3F47E2C66479C76=- INDEX0 is required for the first pista, set to 0 seconds +++
0EB14352D4552B3F=- INDEX1 for the first pista must be set to 2 seconds or later +++
49C000EBB4036538=  (audio contenido prior to 2 seconds will be ignored) +++
6E81355EC5648B8C=- minimum pista length is 4 seconds +++
BC6C41CB2754D1BD=  (time between INDEX1 of one pista and INDEX0/INDEX1 of the following pista) +++
7776D20907057EB8=- INDEX1 must be at least 1 frame (1/75 second) after INDEX0, if INDEX0 is defined +++
49ABCDE3BB438B15=- audio is padded with silence to be frame (1/75 second) aligned +++
E7B4C01D859D878F=------------------------------------------------
5AB72F83207053A9=Album and pista metadata is set by project marcador names: +++
6BBBE201B9175533=- marcadores starting with the \"@\" character represent album metadata +++
BA60C210DC82AF27=- marcadores starting with the \"!\" character represent the INDEX0 position for the following \"#\" pista +++
13209DB01A74B4DE=- marcadores starting with the \"#\" character represent pista metadata and the INDEX1 position +++
02C7C209BB2B414E=If there is more than one @ marcador, each one overwrites the values defined by the previous marcador. +++
665E1DF35B7927C4=If there are multiple ! marcadores in a single pista, only the last marcador prior to the # marcador is used. +++
B4F6694CD4A986DB=The number of # marcadores represents the number of CD pistas. +++
0FA774882DC41844=@ marcadores can be anywhere, but the most readable position is at the end of the album. +++
51268751B55CEEBB=If the audio data is too short, ! and # marcadores positioned more than 10 seconds after +++
20B36E06577B195C=the end of the audio will be ignored. +++
68B13B2279FAF08B=Audio will be padded with silence and frame-aligned (1/75 second) until the last used marcador. +++
6FA47A9FFA512DC7=Metadata is in \"KEY1=VALUE1|KEY2=VALUE2|KEY3=VALUE3\" format. +++
